{{nihongo|'''Yukinari Sugawara'''|菅原 由勢|Sugawara Yukinari|born 28 June 2000}} is a Japanese professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right-back]] for {{English football updater|Southamp}} club [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] and the [[Japan national football team|Japan national team]].

Sugawara began his senior career at [[Nagoya Grampus]]. In 2019, he joined [[AZ Alkmaar|AZ]] on loan before joining the club permanently in 2020. Sugawara moved to English club [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] in 2024. He spent the [[2025–26 SV Werder Bremen season|2025–26]] season on loan at [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]]. Sugawara has represented his country at youth and [[Japan national football team|full international]] level.

==Club career==
===Nagoya Grampus===
On 23 February 2018, it was announced that [[Nagoya Grampus]] had registered Sugawara as a player.<ref>{{Cite press release |url=http://nagoya-grampus.jp/news/pressrelease/2018/0223u-18-8.php |title=Nagoya Grampus U-18 Sugawara Yusei and Naruse Shunpei Registered to Top Team (2nd Division Registration) |publisher=Nagoya Grampus Eight |date= 23 February 2018 |accessdate=26 July 2024}}</ref> Sugawara made his debut  the following day, the opening day of the [[2018 J1 League|2018 season]], in a match against [[Gamba Osaka]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Meiji Yasuda Life J1 League Section 1: Gamba Osaka vs Nagoya Grampus|url=http://nagoya-grampus.jp/game/result/2018/0224/report__1vs.html|website=nagoya-grampus.jp|publisher=Nagoya Grampus|access-date=24 February 2018|language=ja|date=24 February 2018|archive-date=29 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190829125055/http://nagoya-grampus.jp/game/result/2018/0224/report__1vs.html|url-status=live}}</ref> At 17 years, 7 months, and 27 days, Sugawara's starting appearance in the J1 League opening match was the second youngest record in history (the youngest being [[Junichi Inamoto]] at 17 years and 6 months).<ref>{{Cite news |date=18 February 2018 |title=Coach Kazama: "Age is No Barrier"…Nagoya's 17-Year-Old DF Sugawara Yusei Impresses in Full Debut |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?238410-238410-fl |accessdate=26 July 2024 |publisher=Gekisaka |archive-date=31 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331204519/https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?238410-238410-fl |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=24 February 2018 |title=風間監督「年齢は関係ない」…名古屋17歳DF菅原由勢が堂々開幕戦フル出場 |trans-title=Coach Kazama: "Age doesn't matter"... Nagoya's 17-year-old defender Yukinari Sugawara impressively plays full time in the season opener. |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?238410-238410-fl |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331204519/https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?238410-238410-fl |archive-date=31 March 2019 |access-date=31 October 2019 |website=gekisaka.jp |publisher=Gekisaka |language=ja}}</ref> On 6 April 2018, Sugawara signed his first professional contract with Nagoya Grampus, the youngest in the club's history to sign a professional deal, at 17 years and 10 months.<ref>{{Cite web |date=14 July 2024 |title=In Profile: Yukinari Sugawara |url=https://www.southamptonfc.com/en/news/article/in-profile-yukinari-sugawara |access-date=6 September 2024 |website=Southampton FC |archive-date=5 August 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240805060348/https://www.southamptonfc.com/en/news/article/in-profile-yukinari-sugawara |url-status=live }}</ref>

====Loan to AZ====
Sugawara joined [[Eredivisie]] club [[AZ Alkmaar|AZ]] on 21 June 2019 on a season-long [[Loan (sports)|loan]].<ref name="huurdeal">{{cite press release|title=Huurdeal Sugawara afgerond|url=https://www.az.nl/nl/nieuws/huurdeal-sugawara-afgerond|website=az.nl|publisher=AZ|access-date=24 February 2018|language=nl|date=21 June 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190630085134/https://www.az.nl/nl/nieuws/huurdeal-sugawara-afgerond|archive-date=30 June 2019}}</ref> He made his first-team debut on 25 July, as a 59th-minute [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] during AZ's 0–0 home draw against [[BK Häcken]] in the [[2019–20 UEFA Europa League#Second qualifying round|second qualifying round]] of the [[UEFA Europa League|Europa League]].<ref name=Soccerway/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2019/07/25/europe/uefa-cup/stichting-az/bollklubben-hacken/3034760/ |title=AZ vs. Häcken 0–0 |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |access-date=31 October 2019 |archive-date=5 November 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191105111818/https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2019/07/25/europe/uefa-cup/stichting-az/bollklubben-hacken/3034760/ |url-status=live }}</ref> At AZ he was mainly utilised as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right back]], where he competed with the older [[Jonas Svensson (footballer)|Jonas Svensson]], and was set to become his future successor.<ref name="huurdeal" /> On 4 August 2019, Sugawara started in the home match against [[Fortuna Sittard]] and scored the final goal in the 84th minute, to make it 4–0 after preliminary work by [[Calvin Stengs]].<ref>{{cite news |title=AZ dankzij 4-0 zege en letter 'A' koploper, traditionele topdrie speelt gelijk |url=https://nos.nl/liveblog/2296264-az-dankzij-4-0-zege-en-letter-a-koploper-traditionele-topdrie-speelt-gelijk.html |access-date=18 November 2020 |work=NOS |date=4 August 2019 |language=nl |archive-date=5 August 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190805015342/https://nos.nl/liveblog/2296264-az-dankzij-4-0-zege-en-letter-a-koploper-traditionele-topdrie-speelt-gelijk.html |url-status=live }}</ref> Both in the league and group stage of the 2019–20 UEFA Europa League, Sugawara was a regular rotational player during the season, while also making some appearances for the reserve team of [[Jong AZ]] in the second-tier [[Eerste Divisie]]. During this season he played 16 league games in which he scored two goals.

===AZ===
On 23 February 2020, it was announced that Sugawara would sign a five-year contract to join AZ permanently from 1 June 2020.<ref>{{cite press release|title=AZ legt Sugawara definitief vast|url=https://www.az.nl/nl/nieuws/az-legt-sugawara-definitief-vast|access-date=18 November 2020|work=[[AZ Alkmaar]]|date=23 February 2020|language=nl|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200223113851/https://www.az.nl/nl/nieuws/az-legt-sugawara-definitief-vast|archive-date=23 February 2020}}</ref> He was awarded by the [[Eredivisie]] in January 2022 and August 2023.

In October 2023, he became the record-holder for the highest number of European appearances for AZ, reaching his 47th game in European competitions during a match against [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]].<ref name="AD1">{{cite news |last1=Kok |first1=Nik |title=Niet Kees Kist of Barry van Galen, maar deze 23-jarige Japanner speelde de meeste Europese duels voor AZ |url=https://www.ad.nl/nederlands-voetbal/niet-kees-kist-of-barry-van-galen-maar-deze-23-jarige-japanner-speelde-de-meeste-europese-duels-voor-az~a2829be6/ |access-date=20 January 2024 |work=Algemeen Dagblad |date=26 October 2023 |language=nl |archive-date=31 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231031112946/https://www.ad.nl/nederlands-voetbal/niet-kees-kist-of-barry-van-galen-maar-deze-23-jarige-japanner-speelde-de-meeste-europese-duels-voor-az~a2829be6/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

=== Southampton ===
On 14 July 2024, Sugawara signed for [[Premier League]] club [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] on a four-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |date=14 July 2024 |title=Saints seal Sugawara signing |url=https://www.southamptonfc.com/en/news/article/saints-seal-sugawara-signing |access-date=14 July 2024 |website=Southampton FC |archive-date=14 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240714092059/https://www.southamptonfc.com/en/news/article/saints-seal-sugawara-signing |url-status=live }}</ref> He became the fourth Japanese in history to sign with the club, after [[Tadanari Lee]], [[Maya Yoshida]] and [[Takumi Minamino]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=In Profile: Yukinari Sugawara |url=https://www.southamptonfc.com/en/news/article/in-profile-yukinari-sugawara |access-date=18 July 2024 |website=Southampton FC |date=14 July 2024 |archive-date=17 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240717122532/https://www.southamptonfc.com/en/news/article/in-profile-yukinari-sugawara |url-status=live }}</ref> On 17 August 2024, Sugawara made his debut for the club in a 1–0 away defeat against [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Coates |first=Charlotte |date=17 August 2024 |title=Newcastle United 1–0 Southampton |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c2041nprd9nt |access-date=17 August 2024 |website=BBC Sport |archive-date=17 August 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240817101504/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c2041nprd9nt |url-status=live }}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club on 31 August 2024 in a 3–1 away defeat against [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Coates |first=Charlotte |date=31 August 2024 |title=Brentford 3–1 Southampton |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cgl28xezy29t |access-date=1 September 2024 |website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

==== Werder Bremen (loan) ====
On 26 August 2025, Sugawara joined [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]] on a season-long loan.<ref>{{Cite web |date=26 August 2025 |title=Sugawara joins Werder Bremen on loan |url=https://www.southamptonfc.com/en/news/article/sugawara-joins-werder-bremen-on-loan |access-date=26 August 2025 |website=Southampton FC}}</ref> The contract includes an option to buy Sugawara at the end of the season.<ref>{{cite web |title=Werder Bremen sign Yukinari Sugawara on loan |url=https://www.werder.de/en/latest/news/first-team/2025-26/sugawara-loan-26082025/ | website =Werder Bremen |access-date=26 August 2025 |date=26 August 2025}}</ref> He made his debut for the club on 30 August in a 3–3 draw with [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=30 August 2025 |title=Werder Bremen stunned Bayer Leverkusen with unlikeliest of comebacks |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/werder-bremen-bayer-leverkusen-match-report-highlights-matchday-2-33759 |access-date=16 May 2026 |website=Bundesliga}}</ref> On 9 May 2026, Sugawara was shown a [[Red card (association football)|red card]] for a foul on [[Bazoumana Touré]] after a VAR review by referee [[Sören Storks]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=9 May 2026 |title=Bazoumana Touré keeps Hoffenheim in UEFA Champions League contention with Werner Bremen win |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/hoffenheim-werder-bremen-match-report-highlights-matchday-33-37300 |access-date=16 May 2026 |website=Bundesliga}}</ref>

==International career==
Sugawara represented [[Japan national under-17 football team|Japan]] at the [[2017 FIFA U-17 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |date=24 September 2017 |title=U-17日本代表 メンバー・スケジュール FIFA U-17ワールドカップ インド2017（10/6～28） |trans-title=U-17 Japan National Team Members & Schedule for the FIFA U-17 World Cup India 2017 (October 6–28). |url=https://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u17_2017/news/00015113// |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191231043350/http://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u17_2017/news/00015113/ |archive-date=31 December 2019 |access-date=24 February 2018 |language=ja}}</ref> He made his debut with the senior [[Japan national football team|Japan national team]] in a friendly 0–0 tie with [[Cameroon national football team|Cameroon]] on 9 October 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2020/10/09/world/friendlies/japan/cameroon/3375543/|title=Japan vs. Cameroon - 9 October 2020 - Soccerway|website=Soccerway|access-date=19 August 2022|archive-date=27 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211227215521/https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2020/10/09/world/friendlies/japan/cameroon/3375543/|url-status=live}}</ref> In March 2023, Sugawara made his first start for Japan against [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]]. In September of the same year, he provided the assist for the first goal against [[Germany national football team|Germany]] and was also the starting point for the second goal.

